Lovren: &quot;It was a brilliant game from everyone, after a short break, everyone is fit. Records are there to be broken, we believed from the first second we were the better team than City.&quot;<br />
<br />
Lovren: &quot;The manager told us to keep playing football and to be aggressive, so we did. We showed many times our character in difficult moments - we needed this win today.&quot;

Klopp: &ldquo;The atmosphere was good, outstanding from the first second from the minute's tribute with the club again showing how respectful they deal with things like that. I'm really happy about that.&rdquo; <br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;It was outstanding, it helps always. it's one of the best places in world football if we're all on our toes. Though to be honest if the atmosphere wasn't good in a game like that then something is really wrong.&quot;
